<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-068-414  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 068 414.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Feb 21 1989 v3 n8 p18(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT MacWEEK Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>SnapJot does windows. (Trillium Software) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Norr, Henry.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Trillium Software (product introduction).andO;Product:   SnapJot (Utility program).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionUtility ProgramsWindowingComputer Accessories.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>SnapJot does windowsandM;Lombard, Ill.andP;  -- SnapJot, a new utility from Trillium Software, lets userseasily copy any part of the Mac screen into a window and then keep it visiblefor easy reference, printing or pasting.andM;The $36 desk accessory creates a selection marquee each time it is invoked.andO;As soon as the user drags across a region of the screen, SnapJot creates amovable window containing an image of the screen area selected.andP;  Multiplewindows can be created by recalling SnapJot from the Apple menu.andM;The contents of the windows can be copied and pasted into documents as a bitmap but not in the original format.andP;  The image can also be printed directlywith the DA, although SnapJot's printing routines are incompatible withSuperLaserSpool, SuperMac Technology's popular print spooler, (A Trilliumrepresentative blamed the problem on tha fact that SnapJot sends colorinformation to the printer, which causes the spooler to crash.)andP;  An image ina SnapJot window can be saved by copying it into another application or DA.andM;Trillium Software is located at 21W171 Coronet Road, Lombard, Ill.andP;  60148;(312) 916-9360.andO;</TEXT></DOC>